div.p:
"Osceola, the bravest chieftain of them all. Micanopee is old, and his arm is
                  weak, but he has chosen Osceola to fill his place! But I must back to the lodge;
                  for a council is to be held, and they will be dumb until Arpiaka speaks!"

"And you must be cheerful, mother. Do not fret and pine, but live and hope for me;
                  grow young again, and be my own pretty mother, whose cheeks I used to pinch to
                  make them rosy!"

"You cursed coward, I'll take her myself!" cried the colonel, springing forward;
                  but he stopped, too, when the pistol barrel was as quietly and steadily turned to
                     his eye.
